3 Logisitic regression

3.1 Concentration model

M1 <- glm(
  cbind(Dead, Exposed-Dead) ~ Concentration, 
  data=beetles,
  family=binomial(logit)
)
summary(M1)

3.2 Null model

M0 <- glm(
  cbind(Dead, Exposed-Dead) ~ 1, 
  data=beetles,
  family=binomial(logit)
)

3.3 Saturated model

M2 <- glm(
  cbind(Dead, Exposed-Dead) ~ factor(Concentration), 
  data=beetles,
  family=binomial(logit)
)

5 Quadratic concentration model

M3 <- glm(
  cbind(Dead, Exposed-Dead) ~ Concentration + I(Concentration^2), 
  data=beetles,
  family=binomial(logit)
)
summary(M3)

5.1 Comparing models

anova(M1, M3, test = "LRT")
AIC(M1, M3)

6 Residuals

beetles <- 
  beetles %>% 
  add_column(
    res_pearson = residuals(M1, type = "pearson"),
    res_deviance = residuals(M1, type = "deviance"),
    res_M3_pearson = residuals(M3, type = "pearson"),
    res_M3_deviance = residuals(M3, type = "deviance")
  )

beetles %>% 
  ggplot(aes(p, res_pearson)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

beetles %>% 
  ggplot(aes(p, res_deviance)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

beetles %>% 
  ggplot(aes(p, res_M3_pearson)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

beetles %>% 
  ggplot(aes(p, res_M3_deviance)) +

  geom_smooth()
